// compute — Tensix Compute kernel
//
// Reads one tile from game_dfb (CB 0), copies it to out_dfb (CB 1).
// This is the Tensix compute thread, generated by TT-Lang from
// ttlang/zork_kernel_hw.py and beautified (renamed v1-v2, added comments).
//
// Stub behaviour (current):
//   Passes the game tile through to the output DFB unchanged using copy_tile.
//   Proves the CB pipeline is wired correctly end-to-end.
//
// Full implementation (future):
//   Replace copy_tile with Z-machine interpreter logic:
//     1. Accumulate all 85 game tiles from game_dfb into interpreter memory.
//     2. Execute ZMachineV3.interpret(100) — run 100 Z-machine instructions.
//     3. Flush text output into out_dfb tiles for dm_writer to send to DRAM.
//
// Key Tensix compute API calls:
//   cb_wait_front  — wait for dm_reader to push a tile into game_dfb
//   cb_reserve_back — reserve space in out_dfb for the output tile
//   copy_tile_init — configure the copy operation (source CB)
//   copy_tile      — copy tile from source CB slot to dst register (index 0)
//   pack_tile      — pack register to destination CB slot
//   cb_pop_front   — release the consumed source tile back to the pool
//   cb_push_back   — signal dm_writer that the output tile is ready

